<HEADLINE>
<P>
UPDATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIEL CERONE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An automated battlefield with wars fought by robots and computers instead of 
humans? That's what viewers of the PBS science series "Nova" will see next 
season in "Smart Weapons," an episode that is being produced by KCET in Los 
Angeles. The episode will examine advances in military hardware that will 
affect the world's balance of power. 
</P>
<P>
The annual World Cup of Figure Skating held in Ottawa, Canada and featuring 20 
Olympic and world figure skaters competing for $250,000 in prize money, will be 
broadcast by ESPN on Dec. 19. 
</P>
<P>
Pat Morita, known for his sage wisdom as Mr. Miyagi in the "Karate Kid" film 
series, has joined Max von Sydow and Judd Nelson in "Hiroshima: Out of the 
Ashes," an NBC movie that is heading into production. 
</P>
<P>
"A Garfield Christmas Special," a half-hour 1987 cartoon special about the 
self-centered, materialistic cat, will be rerun by CBS on Dec. 21 at 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
George C. Scott won kudos in 1984 for turning his Christmas sneer into holiday 
cheer as Ebenezer Scrooge in Charles Dickens' classic "A Christmas Carol." CBS 
will rebroadcast the two-hour movie on Christmas Eve at 9 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
